s=3D"contentPart css-12zi0x1"><h2 id=3D"trapezoid-perimeter-and-angles">Tra=
pezoid perimeter and angles</h2>
<div class=3D"textBlock"><h3>Perimeter</h3>
<p>The perimeter of a polygon, be it <a href=3D"https://www.calctool.org/ot=
her/regular-polygon" class=3D"js-link">regular</a> or irregular, is the <st=
rong>sum of its side lengths</strong>, and <strong>trapezoids</strong> are =
not the exception. Therefore, the <strong>perimeter of a trapezoid is the s=
um of its four sides</strong>:</p>
<p><em><strong>P =3D a + b + c + d</strong></em></p>
<h3>Angles</h3>
<p>Like any other quadrangle, the sum of <strong>angles</strong> in a trape=
zoid is 360 degrees (or 2=CF=80 radians). However, being a trapezoid (i.e.,=
 having a pair of parallel sides) forces an additional property, which says=
 that the pair of angles along one of the legs are supplementary angles. Th=
erefore, their sum must equal 180 degrees (or =CF=80 radians), which in not=
ation from the calculator figure, translates into:</p>
<p><em><strong>=CE=B1 + =F0=9D=9B=BE =3D =CE=B2 + =CE=B4 =3D 180=C2=B0</str=
ong></em></p>
</div></div><div class=3D"contentPart css-12zi0x1"><h2 id=3D"how-to-calcula=
te-trapezoid-area">How to calculate trapezoid area</h2>
<div class=3D"textBlock"><p>A trapezium is like a rectangle that has "falle=
n over" slightly. Therefore, we calculate its area in a similar way to the =
<a href=3D"https://www.calctool.org/math-and-statistics/rectangle" class=3D=
"js-link">area of a rectangle</a>.</p>
<p>To calculate a trapezoid area, use the following formula:</p>
<p><em><strong>A =3D h =C3=97 (a + b)/2</strong></em></p>
<p>where:</p>
<ul>
<li><em><strong>A</strong></em> =E2=80=94 Trapezium area;</li>
<li><em><strong>h</strong></em> =E2=80=94 Trapezoid height; and</li>
<li><em><strong>a</strong></em> and <em><strong>b</strong></em> =E2=80=94 T=
rapezoid bases.</li>
</ul>
<p>You can look at the dimensions in the following image:</p>
</div><picture class=3D"imageBlock__image-align--none" style=3D"width: 50%;=
"><source media=3D"only screen and (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 2) and =
